<br>
Our Guild will most likely be joining the KCoG very soon, and because of this, I am interested in learning as much as I can about the Council.  I've read a lot of posts here that have given me some insights, and I know some of the members from in-game experiences, and if most of the KCoG are like the ones I know, it will be an honor to associate with all of you.<br>
<br>
Now, for my questions.<br>
<br>
I have followed a few of your raids from afar by keeping in constant touch with some of the raid members.  I've read tons and tons of information about raids, from the &quot;easy&quot; dragons ( Vox / Naggy ) up to the end-game mobs, soaking up a vast amount of information such as pulling / clearing strategies, boss-mob encounter strategies, and even TRW ( total raid wipe ) recovery strategies.  Most of the information I have gleaned is from serious guilds that are serious about there raids - everyone has a job and they execute that job, almost like a military unit.<br>
<br>
I've wondered how a KCoG raid could survive POH / POF / Naggy / Vox, etc. with some of the people I see in EQ these days - the ones that I have no problems with labeling &quot;Idiots&quot;.  I'm sure you know the type that I am referring to.<br>
<br>
What does the KCoG do to the people who disrupt raids by challenging raid leadership, who get others killed with their childish antics, who spout garbage in open channels, who whine because not everything is exactly the way that want it, etc?  Do they get one warning and then forever banned from KCoG events?  Does the Guild Leader get a transcript of the problem from someone's log so they can deal with the problem?  Does it just annoy everyone, ranted about in the forums, and not get dealt with?<br>
<br>
I am -very- interested in attending KCoG raids in the future, but if these types of people are allowed to disrupt the raids, I may have to reconsider.  I've read about a recent Naggy raid that seemed to have some problems along these lines, even though the raid was in very capable hands.  Do the people that cause the problems get dealt with, or do they just get griped about in the forums until people forget about the incident(s)?<br>
<br>
I am very excited about meeting all of you in the upcoming months, and wish you well on your next couple of raids, which I won't be able to attend for various reasons.  Good luck on them, and be safe!<br>
 <p>-Zymyool, Officer and WebMaster for the <a href="http://members.cox.net/ancient" target="_blank">Ancient Adventurers</b></a> on the Karana Server<br><br>
Zymyool - 37 Gnomish Enchanter<br>
