<br>
My name is Destructress Fyrestarter, and i am currently leading KCoG Planes raids...   <br>
<br>
 so far i have not had a problem with Discipline... having to be a higher level to enter the planes,  the people tend to be more mature as a player, and know what they are getting into requires alot of effort.<br>
<br>
Also, most of the KCoG members know that we are not loot based.  90% of the people come expecting to die, and expecting NOT to get anything, expecting the raid to go a little slower then the big uber guilds....<br>
........ and when you come with these expectations, you can just hang out, have a good time, kill some baddies, and, if everything goes well,  live and get a little something, maybe just a gem, or something to sell for a little pp, and sometimes good loot.<br>
<br>
the most importaint thing i have gotton out of KCoG, is screenshots and memories....  fun times...learning... the experance in eq where your level doesnt go up, but your satisfaction.... getting to know poeple, getting to know who are the good people, and learning who needs a hard kick in the arse <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
<br>
as far as who leads raids?   i dont know... Kellory was the KCoG planes raid leader for a while.... he did a great job, and i learned alot from him...<br>
<br>
but he had not  lead them for a while.. and i looked into how to do it, asked questions, and blindly jumped into the drivers seat....<br>
<br>
luckly for me i have had some very wonderful people help me in the background.. they know who they are, and the people that go onthe raids know who they are...  they support KCoG , not me personally ( allthough i have made some great friends). <br>
<br>
I enjoy leading Planes raids, but im limited to sundays and some weekdays...  fridays and saturdays are pretty much out of the question...   I like to do a raid every two weeks.. but sometimes will have to skip a week....<br>
<br>
KCoG is a 'open' allience .. meaning, we are allied with every guild on the server...  but the purpose of KCoG is to help the small guild, to help them grow, to learn, to give them a stepping stone, so to speak....<br>
<br>
...i know someday Children of Disorder (my guild *hugs*) will be large enuf to do our own planes dragons and other large target raids.. at which point i will step down as raid leader... but i will ALLWAYS be here to support KCoG, just as my predecessors have ....<br>
<br>
Even Haemish, god bless his soul, who play DAoC exclusivly, comes and checks on us and keeps this web site alive for everyone who wants to use it ... *cheers*<br>
<br>
all in all, and not to sound korny, KCoG is Karana Servers best hope to keep the game fun and  to help us all remember,,,, everyone starts at level 1.<br>
